post_text:
The XC teams competed in the New Summerfield meet this weekend. For the varsity girls, 3 team members finished in the top 10 and received a medal: Marigold Hunter in 1st place followed by Meredith Howell in 3rd place and Danielle Puckett in 7th. Other team members were Alexa Splawn and Yanely Jaimes. The varsity girls team finished in 2nd place. The varsity boys team members were Josh Fort, Wade Gardner, Jamarion Lydia, Christian Howell, and Emanuel Gonzales.

In the middle school division, the MS girls placed 1st as a team! 5 team members placed top 10 and received a medal. Team members were Blair Bristor (1st), Madeline Howell (4th), Payton Wells (5th), Kambry Nelson (6th), Bailey Gibson (7th), and Audree Hinkle.
The MS boys placed 2nd as a team and had 2 team members place in the top 10 and receive a medal, Benny Bristor (7th) and Cason Nichols (10th). Other team members were Braxton Barton, Nathaniel Dowdy and Sean Flood.
text:

Other team members were Alexa Splawn and Yanely Jaimes. The varsity girls team finished in 2nd place. The varsity boys team members were Josh Fort, Wade Gardner, Jamarion Lydia, Christian Howell, and Emanuel Gonzales.

In the middle school division, the MS girls placed 1st as a team! 5 team members placed top 10 and received a medal. Team members were Blair Bristor (1st), Madeline Howell (4th), Payton Wells (5th), Kambry Nelson (6th), Bailey Gibson (7th), and Audree Hinkle.
The MS boys placed 2nd as a team and had 2 team members place in the top 10 and receive a medal, Benny Bristor (7th) and Cason Nichols (10th). Other team members were Braxton Barton, Nathaniel Dowdy and Sean Flood.

post_text:
Troup Athletic summer workouts are going to take a week off, July 6th-10th. We are going to close all facilities from July 3rd-July 12th and will continue back July 13th. So far, everything has gone really well, kids have been doing great, and we have had no problems. We are taking this week per the recommendation of the UIL and feel like it is important for our athletes to get a break as we plan on Aug. 3rd start date for fall sports. We want to put the athletes in the best possible situation to be able to go forward Aug. 3rd. Thank you for all you have done this summer to make Troup Athletics better and we will continue to put the best interest of our athletes first. Enjoy the break and let's plan on having all Tigers and Lady Tigers ready to go back to work on Monday July 13th at 8:00 am.

Coach Eastman

shared_text:
Troup Independent School District
June 8 at 12:23 PM ·

Troup Student Anglers had 3 teams compete in the THSBA Regional Fishing Tourney yesterday on Lake Tawakoni. 130 teams from the East & Northeast divisions qualified for Regionals. The three Troup teams were - Jordan LeBeff & Joseph Daily, Layne Boyer & Brayden Vess, and Jace Lovelady & Dalton Smith.

The tourney was a 3 fish limit and the top 54 teams qualified for the state tourney. Layne & Brayden finished with a 2 fish stringer of 8.48’ and Jace & Dalton finished in 7th place with a 3 fish stringer of 11.11’. This qualified both teams for the state fishing tourney on Lake Belton July 25-26.

Jace & Dalton also finished the regular fishing season as the 2nd place team (out of 139 teams) for the East Division in points for Angler of the Year.

Troup Lady Tiger Softball
April 17 at 5:00 PM ·

I just want all my girls to know how much fun this season has been for me and how many great memories that we made in such a short period of time. Ashley, Liley and Kacie this May be the end of your softball careers but it is not “the end”. It is only the beginning of the rest of your life. You three girls are going to do great things no doubt. And you have the upper hand here, you will be sure to live life to the fullest and never take anything for granted because you will have known first hand what it feels like to have something you love so much taken away from you. I am proud of each and every one of my girls and how they have been staying in contact these past couple weeks. I hope that we will continue to do so until we are able to meet face to face again. Much love from Coach Weeks and Coach Goode. We couldn’t have asked for a better, more fun, more caring and unique group of girls this year!

In compliance with Governor Abbot's order for schools to continue distance learning until May 4, Troup ISD campuses will remain closed. Troup ISD will continue to offer at-home learning opportunities and free student lunches during this time. We are following all recommended safety precautions at pick-up locations, and will continue to monitor and adjust as needed.

We realize that this is a difficult time for many. As a school district, our priority will always be the safety and security of our students, staff, and community as a whole.

Stay Safe.

post_text:
The Troup Lady Tigers hosted Brownsboro in their first home game of the season tonight. The Lady Tigers came from behind in the 6th inning to tie the game up 1-1. Going into extra innings for a second time this week, the Lady Tigers took the win in the bottom of the 8th inning with a walk of, by Jessie Minnix, that allowed for Lindsay Davis to score the winning run. The Lady Tigers did a much better job tonight putting the ball into play and taking care of business in the batters box. Lindsay Davis picked up her first win of the season, throwing the complete 8 inning game, while walking 1 batter, giving up just 1 hit, no earned runs and sending 17 back to the dugout with strike outs. I wouldn't be doing the team justice if I gave credit to just a few players, because it was a complete team effort. The loud and rowdy crew in our dugout kept our spirits up and the game alive! The Lady Tigers are now 1-1 on the season. Troup is set to host Eustace on Monday with a 6PM game start. Come on out and support our girls. They are so much fun to watch!
Coach Weeks
